div.p:
1. That I have turn'd the Plot into Ridicule;
               The Articles against me. and put
an Affront upon King, Lords, and Commons in so doing.

It is again, to be consider'd; that the Tenses WAS,
and HAVE BEEN, have a regard to what is past;
and that the Word Parliaments, (in the Plural Number,
cannot be understood of That which is now in Being;


Which was not neither, at the time when This was
Written, in the Exercise of its Power.
